body:
This looks a bit odd. what is the exact geth version number? 

The first example: 
```

2023-03-07 07:40:12 INFO [03-07|06:40:12.381] Starting work on payload                 id=0xd3846dc3543749fc
2023-03-07 07:40:12 INFO [03-07|06:40:12.451] Updated payload                          id=0xd3846dc3543749fc number=16,774,703 hash=91f794..1d8a91 txs=136  gas=14,644,528
// After 70ms, we created the first non-empty version, reaching 14.6M gas


// This is weird though: starting work on the same identical payload : 
//
2023-03-07 07:40:12 INFO [03-07|06:40:12.473] Starting work on payload                 id=0xd3846dc3543749fc
2023-03-07 07:40:12 INFO [03-07|06:40:12.535] Updated payload                          id=0xd3846dc3543749fc number=16,774,703 hash=f66e35..4463d8 txs=134  gas=14,426,012
// And the new update we just made is worse than the previous one


...
2023-03-07 07:40:24 INFO [03-07|06:40:24.382] Stopping work on payload                 id=0xd3846dc3543749fc reason=timeout
// And eventually they time out
```
Seems to me that teku starts work, but doesn't actually collect it -- and eventually geth just times out and discards it.
